Some international companies are already distancing themselves.
"The Ebola epidemic is not only a medical crisis, but also an economic one," said Donald Kaberuka, head of the African Development Bank.
Liberia is hardest hit
"It's a total disaster, we're losing a lot of money," says Alhaji Bamogo, who sells clothes at Liberia's capital, Monrovia, the second-largest market.
